<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7685445>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7–11. Terminalia, head and pronotum of Habaek koreanus gen. n., sp. n.—7: male terminalia, dorsal view; 8: same, lateral view; 9: female terminalia, ventral view; 10: ventral edge of female terminalia, lateral view; 11: head and pronotum, dorsal view (holotype)—scales 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7685445/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7685443>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–6. Somatic characters of Habaek koreanus gen. n., sp. n.—1: ventral sclerites of the female thorax (P: prothoracic; Me: mesothoracic; M: metathoracic–Bs: basisternum; Cx: coxa; Etn: eutrochantin; Fs: furcasternum; Fsa: furcasternal arm or furcal pit; Fsp: furcasternal pit or stem of mesosternal ridge; Gv: gill vestige; Lcs: lateral cervical sclerite; Pfs: postfurcasternum; Pn: pronotum; Po: postcoxal bridge; Pr: precoxal bridge; Prs: presternum; Ss: spinasternum; St1: sternum 1; Tn: trochantin; Tr: trochanter); 2: female forewing; 3: female hindwing (A: anal vein; a: anal crossvein; arc: arculus; C: costa; Cu: cubital vein; cu-a: cubitoanal crossvein; h: humeral crossvein; M: medial vein; m-cu: mediocubital crossvein; R: radial vein; r-m: radiomedial crossvein; Sc: subcosta); 4: female head, ventral view (arrow indicates submental gill); 5: female forewing; 6: male forewing—scales 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7685443/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

